The paper discusses the use of genetic algorithms (GAs) for optimization problems, which is a topic commonly studied in the subfield of computational intelligence (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on population diversity and its impact on GA performance suggests a connection to the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of rigorous runtime analysis and comparison of different diversity mechanisms suggests a connection to the subfield of theoretical computer science (cs.DS) and game theory (cs.GT).
